sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User/kubectl
    participant APIServer as Kubernetes API Server<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Webhook as CodeFlare Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+<br/>mTLS
    participant Controller as CodeFlare Controller
    participant KubeRay as KubeRay Operator
    participant RayHead as Ray Head Pod<br/>8265/TCP HTTP
    participant OAuthProxy as OAuth Proxy Sidecar<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant OAuthServer as OpenShift OAuth<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Browser as User Browser

    Note over User,KubeRay: Flow 1: Create RayCluster Resource
    User->>APIServer: POST RayCluster CR<br/>Auth: User kubeconfig
    APIServer->>Webhook: POST /mutate-ray-io-v1-raycluster<br/>mTLS (API Server client cert)
    Webhook->>APIServer: Return mutated CR<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    APIServer->>Webhook: POST /validate-ray-io-v1-raycluster<br/>mTLS
    Webhook-->>APIServer: Validation response
    APIServer->>Controller: Watch event (CREATE)<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Controller->>APIServer: Create OAuth Proxy deployment<br/>Create NetworkPolicies<br/>Create Routes/Ingress<br/>Create Secrets (OAuth, TLS, CA)
    Controller->>KubeRay: Coordinate RayCluster (via API)<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    KubeRay->>APIServer: Create Ray pods and services

    Note over Browser,RayHead: Flow 2: Access Ray Dashboard (OpenShift)
    Browser->>OAuthProxy: GET https://{route}/dashboard<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.3
    OAuthProxy->>OAuthServer: OAuth2 authentication flow<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    OAuthServer-->>OAuthProxy: OAuth token
    OAuthProxy->>RayHead: Proxy request to dashboard<br/>HTTP/8265 (no encryption)
    RayHead-->>OAuthProxy: Dashboard response
    OAuthProxy-->>Browser: HTTPS response

    Note over User,RayHead: Flow 3: Ray Client Connection (mTLS)
    User->>RayHead: ray.init("ray://{host}:10001")<br/>TCP/10001 mTLS<br/>Client Certificate
    RayHead-->>User: Connection established<br/>mTLS encrypted

    Note over APIServer,Controller: Flow 4: Metrics Collection
    APIServer->>Controller: GET /metrics (8080/TCP)<br/>HTTP ServiceAccount Token
    Controller-->>APIServer: Prometheus metrics

    Note over User,KubeRay: Flow 5: AppWrapper Scheduling (when enabled)
    User->>APIServer: POST AppWrapper CR<br/>User kubeconfig
    APIServer->>Webhook: POST /mutate-workload-codeflare-dev-v1beta2-appwrapper<br/>mTLS
    Webhook-->>APIServer: Mutated AppWrapper
    APIServer->>Webhook: POST /validate-workload-codeflare-dev-v1beta2-appwrapper<br/>mTLS
    Webhook-->>APIServer: Validation OK
    Controller->>APIServer: Create Kueue Workload CR<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    APIServer->>KubeRay: Kueue schedules workload<br/>AppWrapper creates RayCluster
